1
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:06,040
You are already starting to love your car too much.

2
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:11,160
Everyone has things they love, right?

3
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:14,840
Isn't it enough to love only me?

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:18,320
It's different.

5
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:19,960
How is it different?

6
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,400
This car is something I love,

7
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,040
but you are the one I love.

8
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,480
Seriously,

9
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:38,960
why do you enjoy driving racing cars?

10
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:43,200
Actually...

11
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,640
I don't like racing with anyone.

12
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:49,440
I like driving alone.

13
00:00:51,520 --> 00:00:53,240
It helps me focus more.

14
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,920
Most importantly,

15
00:00:57,240 --> 00:01:00,280
it's another way for me to let out my anger.

16
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,920
To the extent that you own a racetrack,

17
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:07,960
your anger level must be really high.

18
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:09,240
Of course.

19
00:01:10,520 --> 00:01:12,040
If it's me

20
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,560
who wants to vent my anger,

21
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:17,360
I'll shout it out.

22
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,120
For instance...

23
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,600
Go to hell!

24
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:25,000
- Dumbass! - Hey! Hey, calm down.

25
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:30,040
You're going to startle everyone around here! Why did you do that?

26
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,200
Just showing you an example.

27
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:36,560
That was a pretty harsh example. Did someone just make you angry?

28
00:01:38,040 --> 00:01:40,720
I rarely see you driving racing cars these days,

29
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:43,200
which means you're in a good mood, aren't you?

30
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:46,040
Mm. I don't have much to be angry about.

31
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:49,280
Since we've been together,

32
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:54,160
I smile and laugh more than I get angry.

33
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,520
Wanna try driving?

34
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:02,920
Me? Driving?

35
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:05,200
But you're not dressed for it.

36
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:08,480
- Hey, you. - Hmm?

37
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,400
Next week,

38
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:14,520
my mother will organize a charity event to help eliminate violence against women.

39
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,240
Umm...

40
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,400
That sounds interesting.

41
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:22,480
Are you going?

42
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:24,000
Of course I am.

43
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,080
Then... do I have to go?

44
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,200
Yes, you do.

45
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,600
Sometimes,

46
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:37,360
that might be the right time for us to make our relationship public.

47
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:45,920
If I go there,

48
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,640
won't I steal the spotlight from your mother?

49
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,200
I don't care.

50
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:54,600
I care more about having our relationship recognized by the public.

51
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,400
Can I get a hug?

52
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,240
That's a pretty good idea.

53
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:16,360
I think your mother would probably like a big, dramatic moment.

54
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,920
Yes, Kee.

55
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:45,440
What I asked you to look into,

56
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:46,800
how's it going?

57
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,440
I have already looked into it.

58
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,480
It might not be true.

59
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:56,960
As far as I know, Ms. Ruwajee doesn't like Ms. Weiling at all

60
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:00,640
and doesn't want her to marry her brother.

61
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,560
This might be a made-up story

62
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:05,040
to bring about the inheritance lawsuit.

63
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,520
I shouldn't have believed a drunk person.

64
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,680
If we can't use their infidelity,

65
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:23,560
then we focus on their confidants,

66
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:27,320
those they trust the most.

67
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,440
They just made a token protest.

68
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,920
They probably want land values ​​to rise.

69
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,080
Get out! [Don't cheat us!]

70
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,080
[All our land was taken from us] [You cheating fat cat! We won't move!]

71
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,400
- Get out! - Go away! We will not leave!

72
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,880
Can you hear me?! Get out!

73
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,880
You! Greedy capitalists!

74
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:56,320
We won't go away!! [Don't cheat us! Our land! Our villages!]

75
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,520
We'll stay here!

76
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,400
Get lost, you pigs! Get out! [Greedy investors]

77
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,240
Do what we usually do.

78
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,600
But don't go over budget.

79
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,200
They'll get used to asking for more and more.

80
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,280
Or you can talk to their leaders.

81
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,560
He may help persuade the others.

82
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,680
Yes, ma'am. I'll take care of it.

83
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:22,400
What about the other things I asked you to look into?

84
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,960
You mean...

85
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,000
Everything.

86
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,880
About your friend,

87
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:33,600
I haven't found anything yet.

88
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,760
But if it's about Arisa,

89
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:41,920
I've found something that can be used against her.

90
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,280
What is it?

91
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,760
Well...

92
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,960
Mom, can I talk to you?

93
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:00,840
Yes?

94
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:07,640
I just want to talk about the upcoming charity event.

95
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,200
Why?

96
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,680
Well,

97
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:13,880
I want to use this chance to introduce Arisa

98
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,560
as my lover.

99
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,720
Did she ask for this?

100
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,080
No, she didn't.

101
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,680
It's what I want.

102
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:31,360
I want to make it public that I'm in a relationship.

103
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,240
Haven't you ever wanted

104
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,720
to hold someone's hand

105
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,520
and tell everyone they're your loved one?

106
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,680
Lalin,

107
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:52,600
I don't want you to be too sure.

108
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,320
If you two ever break up,

109
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,920
we'll become a laughingstock.

110
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:02,000
Why do you keep thinking we're going to break up?

111
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,680
What's behind that?

112
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:11,600
I just want you to give Arisa a chance.

113
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:15,240
How much does she have to prove herself to you?

114
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:20,280
Even giving us money to pay off the debt still doesn't satisfy you, huh?

115
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,720
No one

116
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:27,320
gives anything without expecting something in return.

117
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,760
We just don't know what that expectation is yet.

118
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:37,920
Lalin,

119
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,480
it's up to you.

120
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,800
Sometimes, I also think

121
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:48,120
I can't always protect you.

122
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,960
You'll have to learn on your own.

123
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,400
And one day, you'll understand

124
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,680
why I did

125
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,120
what I did.

126
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,080
I've already looked into Wit.

127
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:27,800
His family

128
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,680
has worked for Weiling since his father's time.

129
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,840
After his parents died,

130
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,120
he took over

131
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:37,760
and has sincerely worked for Weiling

132
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,040
for many years.

133
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,960
What's he like?

134
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,520
In terms of work,

135
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,920
he's like Weiling's personal assistant.

136
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:53,640
But in terms of his personal life,

137
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:58,000
he's been living with his girlfriend for many years.

138
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:04,680
So, is there any weakness we can use against him?

139
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,360
That would be his girlfriend.

140
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:12,240
From what I've found out about him,

141
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:28,000
their relationship

142
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:33,640
doesn't seem like a normal one.

143
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,040
Leave it to me.

144
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:16,760
Hello.

145
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,200
I'm a freelance artist

146
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,960
looking for a gallery space.

147
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,280
Are you available?

148
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:26,960
Ah...

149
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,800
Yeah, but...

150
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:32,400
our gallery has capacity limits

151
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:34,640
since I'm the only one responsible for it.

152
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:37,320
If there are too many people, I can't handle them all.

153
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,440
If you can't accept this condition, I can recommend some other galleries.

154
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:42,000
That's fine.

155
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,160
Just a small number.

156
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,640
Only one person.

157
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:55,480
I didn't know there was such a beautiful gallery around here.

158
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,960
And there's still plenty of availability.

159
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:01,440
We don't really host events very often.

160
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:04,080
I used to take on big projects, but I couldn't handle them.

161
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,960
So I only take on small projects.

162
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,800
My husband kept complaining to me about it.

163
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:15,000
Doing it alone and still handling everything this well

164
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:16,560
is already great.

165
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,640
Are you alright?

166
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:31,160
I'm kind of clumsy.

167
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,120
I often bump into things,

168
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,760
so I sometimes get hurt.

169
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,600
Excuse me, let me have a look.

170
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,120
This kind of bruise is from...

171
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,760
fingerprints.

172
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,280
This is my personal matter.

173
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,760
Once you've had a look around,

174
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:54,480
let me know if you're interested.

175
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:57,200
I have something to take care of. Thank you for coming.

176
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,360
Your husband did that, didn't he?

177
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,520
You've been through all this, and you still haven't broken up with him?

178
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,760
You hope he'll change, right?

179
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,200
I'm sorry for meddling in your personal matters,

180
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:27,040
but my father taught me that

181
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,720
a man who hurts a woman

182
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:31,080
or hits his wife

183
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,360
is not a good man.

184
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:35,680
You don't need to keep him in your life.

185
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:40,800
You... You're not with him, are you?

186
00:13:42,680 --> 00:13:43,680
No, I'm not.

187
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:46,160
I'm not with him.

188
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:52,600
It's okay, I won't hurt you.

189
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:00,600
Hey...

190
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:05,320
I'm strong enough to protect you.

191
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,080
You just have to tell me.

192
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,840
Who did this to you?

193
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,640
And what has happened to you?

194
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,560
Tell me everything.

195
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:30,000
Wit is a devilish person.

196
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:32,560
He hits me every day.

197
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,920
Especially when he's stressed from work,

198
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:41,360
he hits me even more.

199
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:44,120
He always checks my phone,

200
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:47,240
including my call history.

201
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,920
I don't have any money.

202
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,360
I tried to leave,

203
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,080
but I didn't know where to go.

204
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:01,360
I have no relatives.

205
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:05,720
He is the only family I have.

206
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:10,120
Have you ever tried to file a complaint?

207
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:15,200
Yes, I have.

208
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,040
But it didn't help.

209
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:21,800
The police said it was a domestic matter

210
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,960
and just tried to mediate.

211
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,720
After that day,

212
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:29,240
I've been beaten even more severely,

213
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:33,400
so I think I'd better just keep enduring it.

214
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:38,600
Don't worry.

215
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:42,160
I'll help you.

216
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,960
But you need to listen to me.

217
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:50,000
Go home and wait for him like usual.

218
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:52,680
Don't be afraid.

219
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:54,920
I understand you.

220
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:59,400
But now we need damning evidence against him.

221
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,000
Stay strong.

222
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,160
Be patient.

223
00:16:08,040 --> 00:16:09,680
I promise you,

224
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,200
he'll never lay a hand on you again.

225
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:23,680
Can you really help me get out of this?

226
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:57,370
Hey...

227
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:59,410
What do you think of this dress?

228
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:05,690
Why aren't you saying anything?

229
00:17:06,210 --> 00:17:07,450
You're stressing me out.

230
00:17:08,650 --> 00:17:10,850
Beautiful. It suits you.

231
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:13,610
You said that about the last one, too.

232
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:17,930
Well, you look good

233
00:17:18,290 --> 00:17:19,930
in anything you wear.

234
00:17:24,370 --> 00:17:26,770
Since it's our first event together as a couple,

235
00:17:28,410 --> 00:17:29,930
I think this dress is perfect.

236
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:32,090
Okay.

237
00:17:32,130 --> 00:17:33,690
I'll go with this one, then.

238
00:17:36,050 --> 00:17:37,810
We'll go with this one.

239
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:40,490
Please send it to us.

240
00:17:40,850 --> 00:17:42,530
Noted. Thank you so much.

241
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:47,410
So beautiful.

242
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:52,290
Do you like it?

243
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:55,890
Yeah, I like this one.

244
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:01,650
Hey, could you please zip it up for me?

245
00:18:52,850 --> 00:18:54,090
Hey!

246
00:18:54,330 --> 00:18:55,330
Hmm?

247
00:18:56,370 --> 00:18:58,130
Are you teasing me?

248
00:19:04,610 --> 00:19:06,930
I almost let my intrusive thoughts win,

249
00:19:07,530 --> 00:19:09,570
but I didn't.

250
00:19:11,330 --> 00:19:12,930
You're such a tease.

251
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:14,970
Better watch it.

252
00:19:15,850 --> 00:19:19,130
If it's my turn, you'll fall into a trap.

253
00:19:20,450 --> 00:19:21,210
Here,

254
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:22,810
let me zip it up for you.

255
00:19:23,610 --> 00:19:25,010
No more.

256
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:27,650
Hey!

257
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:33,530
So refreshing.

258
00:19:35,490 --> 00:19:37,250
Is there anywhere you want to go today?

259
00:19:38,250 --> 00:19:40,570
I don't have any plans yet,

260
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:43,690
but the only plan I have right now

261
00:19:43,730 --> 00:19:45,490
is to stick with you.

262
00:19:46,130 --> 00:19:49,010
And you? Is there anywhere you wanna go?

263
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:52,970
Yes.

264
00:19:56,890 --> 00:19:59,090
There is a place I want you to visit.

265
00:20:13,570 --> 00:20:18,250
In a few more days, it'll be 20 years since I last saw you both.

266
00:20:24,010 --> 00:20:26,570
Hello, Mother and Father.

267
00:20:27,130 --> 00:20:28,690
I'm Lalin,

268
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:31,010
Arisa's girlfriend.

269
00:20:35,890 --> 00:20:40,570
In the near future, Lalin will become part of our family.

270
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,050
If you were here,

271
00:20:46,610 --> 00:20:48,490
things would be easier.

272
00:20:50,130 --> 00:20:53,970
Unfortunately, I never got the chance to meet your parents.

273
00:20:54,850 --> 00:20:58,810
But I know they must have done a wonderful job raising you.

274
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,570
Greedy investors, get out!

275
00:21:19,610 --> 00:21:20,330
Get out!

276
00:21:20,370 --> 00:21:21,210
Get out! [Greedy investors!]

277
00:21:21,690 --> 00:21:24,770
Get out! Get out!! [Stop exploiting people!]

278
00:21:24,810 --> 00:21:26,570
- Get out! - Get out!

279
00:21:26,610 --> 00:21:28,570
Get out!! Get out!

280
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:30,730
If you won't get out, then come out and talk to us!

281
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:37,690
Get out!

282
00:21:37,810 --> 00:21:38,650
Let's calm down first, everyone.

283
00:21:38,690 --> 00:21:39,930
- Please calm down. - You! Greedy capitalists!

284
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:42,130
Why on earth are you opening so many malls? Huh?!

285
00:21:42,170 --> 00:21:43,970
What the f*ck do you need so much space for?

286
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:46,370
We've been living here since our great-grandparents' time!

287
00:21:46,570 --> 00:21:48,490
Where the hell are we supposed to go if we can't live here?!

288
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:50,810
Everyone, calm down. Please, calm down.

289
00:21:51,170 --> 00:21:54,810
We don't have any bad intentions.

290
00:21:56,330 --> 00:21:59,690
We just want to develop this land

291
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:02,970
and improve your quality of life.

292
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:04,970
Improve our quality of life?

293
00:22:05,170 --> 00:22:06,970
You want to improve yours! What about us?

294
00:22:07,010 --> 00:22:08,970
You build shopping malls! You build sidewalks!

295
00:22:09,050 --> 00:22:11,450
You install air conditioners for your own comfort! But what about us?!

296
00:22:11,490 --> 00:22:13,250
- Exactly! - We've got nothing at all!

297
00:22:14,050 --> 00:22:15,330
You must get out!

298
00:22:15,930 --> 00:22:20,210
I understand you. I understand that everyone here is deeply connected to this land.

299
00:22:21,810 --> 00:22:23,530
But I just want to say that

300
00:22:24,650 --> 00:22:25,890
"home"

301
00:22:26,490 --> 00:22:28,970
means the people who live there.

302
00:22:29,090 --> 00:22:30,410
What the f*ck are you saying?

303
00:22:30,530 --> 00:22:32,090
Home is home.

304
00:22:32,290 --> 00:22:33,290
You're demolishing our homes!

305
00:22:33,410 --> 00:22:34,570
We have nowhere to live!

306
00:22:34,610 --> 00:22:36,250
Where on earth can we live?!

307
00:22:36,330 --> 00:22:38,170
Right! That's right!

308
00:22:38,170 --> 00:22:38,970
Get the hell out of here!

309
00:22:39,050 --> 00:22:40,850
I just want to let you know

310
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:45,170
that everyone has the right to start a family anywhere.

311
00:22:45,570 --> 00:22:46,850
Our company

312
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:48,450
would like to offer

313
00:22:49,330 --> 00:22:50,970
compensation to everyone.

314
00:22:51,410 --> 00:22:53,130
One million baht for each family.

315
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:01,370
Everyone!

316
00:23:02,730 --> 00:23:05,770
If you want the million baht, go ahead and take it.

317
00:23:06,010 --> 00:23:07,210
But I'm not taking it!

318
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:08,530
Me, too!

319
00:23:08,690 --> 00:23:11,170
The money isn't enough!

320
00:23:11,410 --> 00:23:13,170
It's just hush money to keep us quiet!

321
00:23:13,210 --> 00:23:14,650
- Yes! - Right!

322
00:23:14,810 --> 00:23:16,170
We're not gonna move!!

323
00:23:16,210 --> 00:23:19,130
- We don't want it! - We're not gonna move!

324
00:23:19,210 --> 00:23:21,690
- Calm down, please. - Please, calm down.

325
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:25,050
Please, calm down first.

326
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:26,930
Calm down. Calm down.

327
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:33,730
Calm down. Take it easy.

328
00:23:33,770 --> 00:23:36,090
- Go! - Get out!

329
00:23:36,170 --> 00:23:37,770
Calm down. Everyone, please calm down.

330
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:48,090
Hey, what's up?

331
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:50,050
I'm in the alley now.

332
00:23:50,210 --> 00:23:51,210
Yeah.

333
00:23:51,610 --> 00:23:52,930
I already bought it.

334
00:23:53,050 --> 00:23:54,170
Mhm.

335
00:24:23,770 --> 00:24:25,050
Is the A/C broken?

336
00:24:25,450 --> 00:24:26,930
Yes, it is.

337
00:24:34,330 --> 00:24:36,330
Why didn't you call the technician this afternoon?

338
00:24:38,770 --> 00:24:40,050
Doing repairs this late at night

339
00:24:40,330 --> 00:24:41,970
means I can't get any rest.

340
00:24:42,170 --> 00:24:43,610
It just broke,

341
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:45,810
so I called the technician.

342
00:24:47,370 --> 00:24:48,370
It's done.

343
00:25:03,290 --> 00:25:04,650
Thank you so much.

344
00:25:16,410 --> 00:25:17,930
What were you thinking,

345
00:25:18,250 --> 00:25:19,450
calling the technician this late?

346
00:25:21,770 --> 00:25:24,170
You really want to be alone with another man that much?

347
00:25:25,570 --> 00:25:28,690
Are you crazy? You're overthinking it.

348
00:25:29,090 --> 00:25:30,610
How can I not?

349
00:25:31,290 --> 00:25:32,730
Look at what you've done.

350
00:25:34,250 --> 00:25:36,050
I work so hard for you,

351
00:25:36,130 --> 00:25:37,650
and this is what I get?

352
00:25:38,490 --> 00:25:39,810
I don't want to talk to you anymore.

353
00:25:39,930 --> 00:25:41,450
- Talk to me first. - Let go! Let go of me!

354
00:25:41,490 --> 00:25:42,810
Shut the hell up!

355
00:26:03,090 --> 00:26:04,170
Pin...

356
00:26:05,370 --> 00:26:06,570
I'm sorry.

357
00:26:21,970 --> 00:26:23,850
Hello, Ms. Weiling.

358
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:26,490
Where are you guys going?

359
00:26:27,690 --> 00:26:29,810
Honestly, you should teach Lalin how to work.

360
00:26:30,330 --> 00:26:31,610
Now that my daughter has a partner,

361
00:26:31,810 --> 00:26:33,650
I just hope you'll have a good future together.

362
00:26:35,690 --> 00:26:38,490
You make it sound like Lalin is still a kid.

363
00:26:39,370 --> 00:26:41,490
She knows what she's doing.

364
00:26:43,930 --> 00:26:44,930
Anyway,

365
00:26:45,090 --> 00:26:47,170
I heard you want to come to the charity event

366
00:26:47,810 --> 00:26:49,290
and go public with your relationship.

367
00:26:50,410 --> 00:26:52,090
Do you have any surprises for me?

368
00:26:52,970 --> 00:26:54,210
No.

369
00:26:54,770 --> 00:26:57,410
I just do what Lalin wants.

370
00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:01,570
Whether we go public or not

371
00:27:01,890 --> 00:27:03,210
doesn't matter to me.

372
00:27:04,370 --> 00:27:06,650
Being together matters more.

373
00:27:08,090 --> 00:27:09,330
How romantic...

374
00:27:10,090 --> 00:27:13,210
No wonder Lalin's so obsessed with you.

375
00:27:16,890 --> 00:27:18,810
It's not an obsession,

376
00:27:20,210 --> 00:27:21,610
it's love.

377
00:27:23,370 --> 00:27:25,290
It's the kind of love where we take care of each other.

378
00:27:26,210 --> 00:27:27,930
What about you, Ms. Weiling?

379
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:31,450
Have you ever had someone you love and want to take care of?

380
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:42,050
All done! Here I am!

381
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:44,010
What were you guys talking about?

382
00:27:45,570 --> 00:27:48,610
Arisa told me she also wants to go to the charity event.

383
00:27:49,210 --> 00:27:51,050
She said she'll donate ten million baht.

384
00:27:52,250 --> 00:27:53,250
Whoa!

385
00:27:53,490 --> 00:27:55,330
That's a lot!

386
00:27:55,650 --> 00:27:56,770
Awesome!

387
00:28:02,530 --> 00:28:04,530
If it makes you

388
00:28:04,730 --> 00:28:05,930
and your mother happy,

389
00:28:06,370 --> 00:28:07,650
I'll do anything for it.

390
00:28:12,050 --> 00:28:13,690
Come on, let's go.

391
00:28:14,730 --> 00:28:16,130
Goodbye, Mom.

392
00:28:16,210 --> 00:28:17,610
Goodbye.

393
00:29:30,874 --> 00:29:33,314
All you do are things a rich girl would do,

394
00:29:33,634 --> 00:29:35,874
like playing the piano or riding horses.

395
00:29:36,754 --> 00:29:38,154
Of course.

396
00:29:38,274 --> 00:29:40,874
It's called "pretty girl activities."

397
00:29:41,314 --> 00:29:44,954
If you expect me to do something tough, I'm not doing it.

398
00:29:47,834 --> 00:29:49,674
Back in the day,

399
00:29:49,834 --> 00:29:53,114
my father brought me here every week for horse riding lessons,

400
00:29:54,114 --> 00:29:57,514
while my mom often complained that it wasn't useful for business purposes.

401
00:29:59,354 --> 00:30:01,434
I do agree with your father,

402
00:30:01,794 --> 00:30:03,114
since these skills

403
00:30:03,394 --> 00:30:05,914
can be useful someday.

404
00:30:06,994 --> 00:30:08,674
My father was pretty cool, right?

405
00:30:09,354 --> 00:30:12,394
I'll bring you to meet him next time.

406
00:30:12,714 --> 00:30:13,714
Why not?

407
00:30:24,074 --> 00:30:25,194
Did you have fun?

408
00:30:25,474 --> 00:30:26,954
Of course, I did.

409
00:30:28,074 --> 00:30:29,714
Hey! Kee?!

410
00:30:31,554 --> 00:30:33,194
Hey, Kee!

411
00:30:34,474 --> 00:30:36,274
How have you been? Long time no see.

412
00:30:36,474 --> 00:30:37,714
How are you?

413
00:30:38,874 --> 00:30:40,034
I'm good.

414
00:30:41,314 --> 00:30:42,674
And what about you?

415
00:30:43,674 --> 00:30:44,754
Pretty good.

416
00:30:44,874 --> 00:30:46,354
But look at you...

417
00:30:46,754 --> 00:30:48,314
You look better.

418
00:30:48,394 --> 00:30:50,754
Leave your old self behind!

419
00:30:57,994 --> 00:30:58,994
Oh,

420
00:31:01,634 --> 00:31:02,634
this is Lalin.

421
00:31:03,354 --> 00:31:04,554
Hello.

422
00:31:06,994 --> 00:31:10,474
Alright, see you later. I work here.

423
00:31:10,594 --> 00:31:13,514
We should grab a bite sometime. Let me know if you're coming.

424
00:31:20,074 --> 00:31:23,274
Who was that? You seem close to her.

425
00:31:24,714 --> 00:31:25,794
An old friend of mine.

426
00:31:27,834 --> 00:31:31,954
Did she just call you "Kee"?

427
00:31:36,234 --> 00:31:37,634
That's my old name,

428
00:31:37,954 --> 00:31:41,074
but I go by "Arisa" now.

429
00:31:43,874 --> 00:31:45,114
Let's go.

430
00:31:45,154 --> 00:31:46,794
Let's.

431
00:32:04,154 --> 00:32:06,514
How do you know that woman?

432
00:32:07,554 --> 00:32:09,154
Tell me about it.

433
00:32:09,754 --> 00:32:11,514
I'll pay you for that.

434
00:32:19,754 --> 00:32:24,074
Closer, please. Yes, so beautiful.

435
00:32:27,074 --> 00:32:29,914
Is this your official debut

436
00:32:29,994 --> 00:32:33,114
as a real estate couple?

437
00:32:33,794 --> 00:32:35,354
Not really,

438
00:32:36,154 --> 00:32:38,834
and I don't want it to be a big deal.

439
00:32:39,034 --> 00:32:42,274
We just want to let everyone know.

440
00:32:42,314 --> 00:32:43,194
How lovely!

441
00:32:43,234 --> 00:32:44,914
I also want to show respect to Lalin.

442
00:32:47,514 --> 00:32:49,074
So, would Ms. Weiling,

443
00:32:49,114 --> 00:32:54,554
Lalin's mother, be okay with her daughter dating her business rival, Ms. Arisa?

444
00:32:54,754 --> 00:32:57,194
She fully supports our relationship

445
00:32:57,234 --> 00:33:00,354
and never sees Arisa as a rival.

446
00:33:01,754 --> 00:33:04,794
Business can't compete with love.

447
00:33:04,874 --> 00:33:08,354
Aww... so sweet.

448
00:33:08,714 --> 00:33:10,634
Could I take some pictures, please?

449
00:33:10,914 --> 00:33:13,594
-This way. - This way, please.

450
00:33:14,074 --> 00:33:16,394
The information about Arisa's past,

451
00:33:16,794 --> 00:33:17,874
are you sure about it?

452
00:33:20,714 --> 00:33:21,714
Yes, I am.

453
00:33:22,314 --> 00:33:23,314
It's reliable.

454
00:33:25,074 --> 00:33:26,114
Good.

455
00:33:27,274 --> 00:33:28,674
So Lalin will learn

456
00:33:29,394 --> 00:33:30,874
what Arisa is hiding.

457
00:33:41,234 --> 00:33:43,354
Lalin chose her girlfriend well.

458
00:33:43,714 --> 00:33:45,394
I like this one.

459
00:33:46,954 --> 00:33:48,234
I'm also curious

460
00:33:48,354 --> 00:33:50,514
how she managed to get close to you so quickly

461
00:33:50,594 --> 00:33:52,194
that you ended up liking her so fast.

462
00:33:53,834 --> 00:33:55,754
It's fine either way,

463
00:33:56,434 --> 00:34:00,794
but I know Arisa is the one who makes my niece happy.

464
00:34:03,754 --> 00:34:07,634
So, I'll help them get what they want.

465
00:34:10,154 --> 00:34:12,514
I'm not a heartless mother.

466
00:34:13,194 --> 00:34:16,794
If she loves a good person, I'll support her without hesitation.

467
00:34:17,154 --> 00:34:18,754
If not,

468
00:34:19,034 --> 00:34:21,314
I'll get rid of her without hesitation.

469
00:34:45,674 --> 00:34:46,754
Hello.

470
00:34:47,914 --> 00:34:51,554
First of all, I would like to thank all of our honored guests

471
00:34:51,714 --> 00:34:54,154
for joining the charity event I organized

472
00:34:54,194 --> 00:34:56,714
to fight violence against women.

473
00:34:57,994 --> 00:34:59,954
I used to know someone

474
00:35:00,194 --> 00:35:04,194
who went through a painful experience in love.

475
00:35:05,714 --> 00:35:06,914
A broken,

476
00:35:07,514 --> 00:35:08,954
divided

477
00:35:09,514 --> 00:35:10,514
family.

478
00:35:12,434 --> 00:35:14,594
That's where my idea came from.

479
00:35:15,914 --> 00:35:17,714
To organize a fundraising event

480
00:35:17,914 --> 00:35:20,034
to help victims of violence

481
00:35:20,514 --> 00:35:22,634
who feel trapped.

482
00:35:23,914 --> 00:35:25,874
I want to give them the courage to leave those situations.

483
00:35:26,394 --> 00:35:28,634
I want them to know that from now on,

484
00:35:29,194 --> 00:35:31,634
they don't have to fight alone anymore.

485
00:35:40,354 --> 00:35:42,394
Speaking of violence,

486
00:35:43,314 --> 00:35:45,554
one of tonight's donors

487
00:35:45,834 --> 00:35:48,914
might know it best,

488
00:35:50,514 --> 00:35:52,514
Ms. Arisa Kulnavee.

489
00:36:01,794 --> 00:36:05,194
She was once sent to a Juvenile Observation and Protection Center

490
00:36:05,514 --> 00:36:06,954
under supervision

491
00:36:07,154 --> 00:36:09,554
due to a violent offense.

492
00:36:11,154 --> 00:36:12,394
So today,

493
00:36:12,674 --> 00:36:15,474
I want to invite Arisa to share her experience

494
00:36:15,514 --> 00:36:17,674
with everyone here.

495
00:37:01,034 --> 00:37:02,034
First of all,

496
00:37:02,394 --> 00:37:04,994
I would like to thank Ms. Weiling

497
00:37:05,434 --> 00:37:07,914
for attempting to bring up my past,

498
00:37:08,194 --> 00:37:09,994
even though I've already moved on from it.

499
00:37:20,234 --> 00:37:21,794
My past

500
00:37:23,714 --> 00:37:27,314
is the biggest lesson of my life,

501
00:37:28,634 --> 00:37:31,114
as it taught me to be strong

502
00:37:32,274 --> 00:37:34,354
and showed me that

503
00:37:34,634 --> 00:37:37,234
everyone can always start a new life.

504
00:37:37,874 --> 00:37:40,554
All we need is someone who gives us a chance.

505
00:37:42,434 --> 00:37:44,994
Everyone wants a chance, right?

506
00:37:49,554 --> 00:37:51,314
I'm lucky

507
00:37:52,034 --> 00:37:53,994
because I've already found that person.

508
00:37:57,074 --> 00:37:58,474
She is Lalin.

509
00:38:04,394 --> 00:38:08,994
Lalin is the only one who wants me to have a better life

510
00:38:11,194 --> 00:38:13,674
and never cares about my past,

511
00:38:14,314 --> 00:38:17,594
no matter how it is brought up.

512
00:38:23,194 --> 00:38:25,874
I'm happy to be able to spend my life with you.

513
00:38:29,754 --> 00:38:32,954
I used to say that to your mother once.

514
00:38:36,714 --> 00:38:38,714
But today...

515
00:38:39,194 --> 00:38:42,114
I'll say it in front of everyone here.

516
00:39:29,114 --> 00:39:30,114
Lalin,

517
00:39:30,994 --> 00:39:32,314
will you marry me?

518
00:39:35,634 --> 00:39:36,514
Yes, I will.

519
00:39:39,034 --> 00:39:40,594
No matter what you've been through,

520
00:39:40,754 --> 00:39:42,634
I'll marry you.

521
00:40:16,474 --> 00:40:18,034
How do you know that woman?

522
00:40:18,634 --> 00:40:20,514
Tell me about it.

523
00:40:20,994 --> 00:40:22,674
I'll pay you for that.

524
00:40:40,194 --> 00:40:41,514
This man

525
00:40:41,954 --> 00:40:44,114
is the one who will pay me

526
00:40:44,194 --> 00:40:47,354
to get your past from me.

527
00:40:49,114 --> 00:40:50,674
Did you tell him anything?

528
00:40:51,074 --> 00:40:52,354
No, I didn't.

529
00:40:52,914 --> 00:40:55,514
You and I have been through so much together.

530
00:40:55,914 --> 00:40:57,314
I'll never betray you.

531
00:41:03,714 --> 00:41:05,594
Why do you want to know about my past?

532
00:41:07,634 --> 00:41:08,874
What about you?

533
00:41:09,794 --> 00:41:12,034
You also looked into Ms. Weiling's past.

534
00:41:14,914 --> 00:41:17,314
So why can't we look into your past?

535
00:41:21,354 --> 00:41:24,674
Ms. Weiling will never show you her weakness for you to use against her.

536
00:41:27,034 --> 00:41:28,594
Ms. Weiling may not have a weakness,

537
00:41:29,674 --> 00:41:31,234
but you do.

538
00:41:36,074 --> 00:41:37,434
What do you mean?

539
00:41:52,474 --> 00:41:53,474
Pin...

540
00:41:57,954 --> 00:41:59,074
I'm sorry.

541
00:42:02,834 --> 00:42:04,154
Thank you so much.

542
00:42:18,834 --> 00:42:20,754
What have you done with Pin?!

543
00:42:23,194 --> 00:42:25,434
She is in a safe place.

544
00:42:26,074 --> 00:42:28,234
A place where she is safe from you.

545
00:42:28,474 --> 00:42:29,874
Don't worry about her.

546
00:42:30,594 --> 00:42:32,474
The only woman you should worry about

547
00:42:32,794 --> 00:42:34,154
is Ms. Weiling.

548
00:42:36,034 --> 00:42:37,194
From now on,

549
00:42:37,554 --> 00:42:39,354
you must work for me.

550
00:42:41,314 --> 00:42:42,314
Otherwise,

551
00:42:42,874 --> 00:42:46,354
you'll never see your beloved wife again.

552
00:42:48,594 --> 00:42:49,594
Oh,

553
00:42:49,954 --> 00:42:51,914
and as for my past you want to know about,

554
00:42:52,434 --> 00:42:53,874
I'll tell you.

555
00:42:55,474 --> 00:42:58,034
But you must remember every single word.

556
00:42:59,074 --> 00:43:01,834
Don't you dare twist any words.

557
00:43:22,034 --> 00:43:23,794
Please take care of Lalin for me.

558
00:44:37,129 --> 00:44:38,289
What big news.

559
00:44:39,889 --> 00:44:41,009
How did you explain yourself?

560
00:44:42,729 --> 00:44:44,169
Why did I have to do that?

561
00:44:45,129 --> 00:44:46,449
The truth remains.

562
00:44:48,049 --> 00:44:50,409
Besides, I haven't done anything wrong.

563
00:44:51,649 --> 00:44:53,409
I've already told the officers everything.

564
00:44:54,769 --> 00:44:56,089
But it already happened.

565
00:44:57,489 --> 00:45:00,329
Being involved with someone who has done an illegal business

566
00:45:01,249 --> 00:45:02,649
is not a minor issue.

567
00:45:02,889 --> 00:45:04,929
Not only you will be affected,

568
00:45:05,409 --> 00:45:07,289
but also the companies you hold shares in

569
00:45:07,529 --> 00:45:08,729
will be investigated, too.

570
00:45:09,689 --> 00:45:10,929
More importantly,

571
00:45:11,569 --> 00:45:12,569
what about Lalin?

572
00:45:14,049 --> 00:45:15,529
Her reputation might also be ruined by this.

573
00:45:19,649 --> 00:45:21,169
Don't worry too much about that,

574
00:45:22,569 --> 00:45:24,729
I won't let this damage her reputation.

575
00:45:26,009 --> 00:45:27,409
I hope that's true.

576
00:45:29,249 --> 00:45:30,609
Soon,

577
00:45:30,809 --> 00:45:32,609
Lalin will finally see

578
00:45:33,249 --> 00:45:34,889
who the real

579
00:45:35,609 --> 00:45:36,609
Arisa is.

580
00:46:06,409 --> 00:46:07,809
It's true, though.

581
00:46:08,289 --> 00:46:10,209
When it comes to a scammer thing,

582
00:46:10,689 --> 00:46:13,209
people are ready to judge you.

583
00:46:13,809 --> 00:46:16,089
It takes ages for the result to come,

584
00:46:16,689 --> 00:46:18,569
and by that time, the news will have spread widely.

585
00:46:20,169 --> 00:46:23,689
The truth comes too late, no one waits to hear it.

586
00:46:25,129 --> 00:46:26,129
I see.

587
00:46:27,049 --> 00:46:29,969
We tend to believe what we want to believe.

588
00:46:30,409 --> 00:46:31,409
You're right.

589
00:46:32,649 --> 00:46:36,329
But at least, you still got Lalin by your side.

590
00:46:38,449 --> 00:46:40,289
When life's ruined,

591
00:46:41,049 --> 00:46:44,169
having someone by your side is so important.

592
00:46:45,569 --> 00:46:49,129
Lalin is just as great as her dad, Thana.

593
00:46:53,649 --> 00:46:55,129
When I was a teenager,

594
00:46:55,209 --> 00:46:57,009
I went to study in the States.

595
00:46:57,529 --> 00:46:59,369
And I fell in love with a foreign guy.

596
00:47:00,649 --> 00:47:03,369
My family really looked down on him.

597
00:47:03,929 --> 00:47:06,049
Eventually, we couldn't make it.

598
00:47:07,129 --> 00:47:09,169
I was told to fly back to Thailand.

599
00:47:09,969 --> 00:47:13,169
My parents did everything so that I couldn't communicate with him.

600
00:47:14,809 --> 00:47:16,329
But there was only Thana,

601
00:47:17,889 --> 00:47:20,089
who said goodbye on my behalf.

602
00:47:21,289 --> 00:47:23,249
He consoled me and everything.

603
00:47:25,169 --> 00:47:28,889
I felt so lucky to have him as a young brother.

604
00:47:32,249 --> 00:47:34,129
But on the day he passed away for good,

605
00:47:35,649 --> 00:47:37,129
I learned that...

606
00:47:38,449 --> 00:47:41,369
life isn't always that kind to us.

607
00:47:43,529 --> 00:47:44,929
From that day onwards,

608
00:47:45,929 --> 00:47:47,969
I had no one else on my side,

609
00:47:48,369 --> 00:47:51,369
no family or friends,

610
00:47:52,569 --> 00:47:54,449
only me.

611
00:47:58,329 --> 00:48:01,209
Have you talked to Weiling?

612
00:48:02,129 --> 00:48:04,769
She's still your sister-in-law, isn't she?

613
00:48:06,969 --> 00:48:10,729
You still can't tell I hate that bitch?

614
00:48:12,049 --> 00:48:15,329
The whole time she was dating my brother,

615
00:48:16,209 --> 00:48:18,569
I knew she was secretly dating someone else.

616
00:48:24,329 --> 00:48:26,049
Acting like a perfect queen.

617
00:48:26,409 --> 00:48:28,449
Scolding me, saying I was a compulsive gambler.

618
00:48:29,929 --> 00:48:32,209
She was no better than me.

619
00:48:35,769 --> 00:48:38,089
Did Mr. Thana know about this?

620
00:48:40,569 --> 00:48:42,409
Just like you said,

621
00:48:42,969 --> 00:48:46,369
we all wanted to believe in what we felt like.

622
00:48:54,129 --> 00:48:56,169
Don't tell Lalin about this.

623
00:48:57,529 --> 00:49:01,289
Let this die with someone old like me.

624
00:49:09,569 --> 00:49:10,849
OK.

625
00:49:20,889 --> 00:49:21,889
Hey...

626
00:49:22,569 --> 00:49:24,129
Is the shop closed?

627
00:49:24,409 --> 00:49:26,609
No, you can come!

628
00:49:47,209 --> 00:49:51,009
♫Happy birthday to you♫

629
00:49:51,449 --> 00:49:55,769
♫Happy birthday to you!♫

630
00:49:56,049 --> 00:50:00,569
♫Happy birthday, happy birthday♫

631
00:50:01,969 --> 00:50:06,649
♫Happy birthday to you♫

632
00:50:08,409 --> 00:50:09,929
Make a wish.

633
00:50:19,809 --> 00:50:21,609
What did you wish?

634
00:50:23,129 --> 00:50:24,969
I wished...

635
00:50:25,049 --> 00:50:26,449
us...

636
00:50:27,129 --> 00:50:28,169
Better not say it.

637
00:50:28,929 --> 00:50:30,729
I'm afraid it won't come true.

638
00:50:34,849 --> 00:50:36,729
I don't think I need to guess

639
00:50:36,969 --> 00:50:38,849
how you found out when my birthday was.

640
00:50:39,449 --> 00:50:41,769
Only Aiy knew about this.

641
00:50:43,129 --> 00:50:45,169
Don't blame her,

642
00:50:46,089 --> 00:50:48,129
I just wanted to surprise you.

643
00:50:49,529 --> 00:50:51,329
I told you,

644
00:50:51,929 --> 00:50:53,529
I'm not into birthdays.

645
00:50:54,449 --> 00:50:56,209
And I don't like surprises either.

646
00:50:59,329 --> 00:51:03,049
I don't know what you've been through in the past.

647
00:51:04,169 --> 00:51:06,169
But it's time...

648
00:51:06,449 --> 00:51:09,689
to recreate good memories.

649
00:51:10,329 --> 00:51:12,969
I hope you can leave bad things behind.

650
00:51:13,289 --> 00:51:15,809
If you can't leave some,

651
00:51:16,209 --> 00:51:18,049
share them with me.

652
00:51:19,769 --> 00:51:23,129
I want to laugh and cry with you.

653
00:51:30,769 --> 00:51:33,129
But the surprise isn't just that.

654
00:51:33,609 --> 00:51:34,649
You got more?

655
00:51:35,129 --> 00:51:37,009
Umm! Follow me.

656
00:52:38,889 --> 00:52:41,849
Can I be your new memory?

657
00:52:43,169 --> 00:52:46,409
A memory that will make you smile forever.

658
00:52:52,289 --> 00:52:53,449
Thanks.

659
00:54:51,889 --> 00:54:56,449
Next week, my mom is holding a violence-against-women charity.

660
00:54:57,049 --> 00:54:58,209
Sometimes,

661
00:54:58,529 --> 00:55:02,609
it's the time we have to open our relationship to public.

662
00:55:03,009 --> 00:55:04,489
For Arisa,

663
00:55:04,569 --> 00:55:06,929
I already got something to attack her.

664
00:55:07,449 --> 00:55:08,249
What is it?

665
00:55:08,929 --> 00:55:10,409
Hey, Kee!

666
00:55:12,329 --> 00:55:13,409
Who is that, dear?

667
00:55:13,689 --> 00:55:15,129
Why do you seem close to her?

668
00:55:15,409 --> 00:55:16,129
An old friend of mine.

669
00:55:16,449 --> 00:55:18,329
How did you know that woman?

670
00:55:18,489 --> 00:55:19,769
Tell me about it.

671
00:55:20,009 --> 00:55:21,209
I'll pay you for that.

672
00:55:21,489 --> 00:55:24,289
So Lalin will know what Arisa hides from her.

673
00:55:24,649 --> 00:55:27,369
No matter how severe your past is,

674
00:55:28,449 --> 00:55:32,209
I want you to know you will always have me by your side.
